ipose tissues. We demonstrate that the resulting depletion of plasma alanine serves as a cue to increase plasma levels of fibroblast growth factor 21 (FGF21) and activates liver-fat communication, leading to the activation of lipolytic genes in adipose tissues. We propose that this skeletal muscle-liver-fat signalling axis may serve as a target for the development of therapies against various metabolic diseases, including obesity.","altmetric_jid":"4f6fa62f3cf058f610008259","authors":["Noriaki Shimizu","Takako Maruyama","Noritada Yoshikawa","Ryo Matsumiya","Yanxia Ma","Naoki Ito","Yuki Tasaka","Akiko Kuribara-Souta","Keishi Miyata","Yuichi Oike","Stefan Berger","Günther Schütz","Shin’ichi Takeda","Hirotoshi Tanaka","Shimizu, Noriaki","Maruyama, Takako","Yoshikawa, Noritada","Matsumiya, Ryo","Ma, Yanxia","Ito, Naoki","Tasaka, Yuki","Kuribara-Souta, Akiko","Miyata, Keishi","Oike, Yuichi","Berger, Stefan","Schütz, Günther","Takeda, Shin'ichi","Tanaka, Hirotoshi"],"doi":"10.1038/ncomms7693","first_seen_on":"2015-04-02T00:24:13+00:00","funders":["niehs"],"issns":["2041-1723"],"journal":"Nature Communications","links":["http://www.nature.com/ncomms/2015/150401/ncomms7693/full/ncomms7693.html","http://www.nature.com/doifinder/10.1038/ncomms7693","http://www.nature.com/ncomms/2015/150401/ncomms7693/full/ncomms7693.html#affil-auth","http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25827749?dopt=Abstract&utm_source=dlvr.it&utm_medium=twitter","http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25827749?dopt=Abstract","http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4396397/"],"pmid":"25827749","pubdate":"2015-04-01T00:00:00+00:00","publisher":"Nature Publishing Group","publisher_subjects":[{"name":"Multidisciplinary","scheme":"era"}],"subjects":["biology","science"],"title":"A muscle-liver-fat signalling axis is essential for central control of adaptive adipose remodelling","type":"article","volume":"6","mendeley_url":"http://www.mendeley.com/research/muscleliverfat-signalling-axis-essential-central-control-a